org.jconfigurations.converters

Class BaseMapConfigurationConverter<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jconfigurations.converters.BaseMapConfigurationConverter<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K -
    V -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ConfigurationConverter<Map<K,V>>, MapConfigurationConverter<K,V>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    HashMapConfigurationConverter

    public abstract class BaseMapConfigurationConverter<K,V>
extends Object
implements MapConfigurationConverter<K,V>
    Handy abstract class that implementations of MapConfigurationConverter can extend. The BaseMapConfigurationConverter will initialize an instance of the Map's implementation class supplied by subclasses by calling its no-arg constructor.
    Author:
    George Aristy
